SIMPLE: outstrip
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outstrip
<hw>Out*strip"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Outstripped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Outstripping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To go
faster than; to outrun; to advance beyond; to leave behind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Appetites which . . . had <qex>outstripped</qex> the hours.</q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He still <qex>outstript</qex> me in the race.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To exceed in development or performance; to surpass
in any competition; to outdo; to outpace{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outsuffer</ent>⟦br⟧
